The paper proposes a method for computing fingerprints of data sets, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science. The focus on fingerprints and their computation suggests that the paper belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) category. Additionally, the use of pseudo-random hashes and the focus on accuracy and confidence suggest that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) category. The use of fingerprints for similarity and rarity computations suggests that the paper may also belong to the databases (cs.DB) category. The focus on the efficiency of the computation suggests that the paper may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category. Finally, the use of fingerprints for analyzing massive data sets suggests that the paper may also belong to the data mining (cs.DM) category.
